article.headline: Albany 62, MD Baltimore Co 50
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Jason Siggers came off the bench to score 18 points, all in the second half, as Albany rallied for a 62-50 America East Conference victory over UMBC on Wednesday. UMBC (7-11, AE 3-4) trailed by as much as 15 points in the first half but came back to take a second-half lead. Albany (11-8, AE 6-2) went ahead for good, 44-39, in the second half on back-to-back three-point field goals by Siggers and Jamar Wilson. Brian Hodges led all scorers with 19 points off the bench and kept UMBC within striking distance on a jumper that closed the gap to 46-45 with 7:12 left. The Great Danes finally seized control with a 14-2 run over the next five minutes. Levi Levine and Wilson each scored nine for the Great Danes, who have won nine of their last 11.
